cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO 

This paper presents a vision and processing system for attention and tracking using a neuromorphic processor and an event-based camera. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves computer vision and machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The attention mechanism and tracking are also related to reinforcement learning and decision-making, which could place the paper in cs.LG (Machine Learning) as well. Finally, the system is designed for robotics applications, which could make it relevant to cs.RO (Robotics).
